# HR Policy FAQ Semantic Cache

**System Name:** HR Policy FAQ Cache

**Purpose:** Cache responses to employee HR policy questions (vacation, benefits, payroll, leave, remote work, expenses, onboarding) to reduce LLM API costs and deliver instant answers.

**Domain:** Internal HR assistant handling common employee inquiries about company policies. Employees frequently ask the same policy questions using varied phrasing — e.g., "How many vacation days do I get?" vs "What's the PTO allowance?" — making this domain ideal for semantic caching.

## Embedding Strategy

- **Model:** `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (sentence-transformers)
- **Dimension:** 384
- **Rationale:** Fast inference, small footprint, and strong performance on short Q&A text typical of HR policy questions. Well-suited for English-language policy queries under 128 tokens.

## Cache Configuration

- **Similarity Threshold:** 0.87 cosine similarity (distance threshold ≈ 0.13)
- **Distance Metric:** Cosine similarity
- **TTL:** 30 days (2,592,000 seconds) — company policies are stable but reviewed monthly
- **Index Type:** HNSW (faster approximate retrieval, good for growing FAQ sets)

## Cache Strategy

**Cache Write Triggers:**
- After successfully generating an LLM response for a cache miss
- Store: `{query_embedding, response_text, category_tag, timestamp}`
- Initial hydration with curated FAQ pairs across all policy categories

**Cache Miss Handling:**
1. Normalize the incoming query (lowercase, trim whitespace)
2. Check semantic cache using the configured distance threshold
3. If miss → call LLM API to generate a response
4. Store the new response in the cache for future hits

**Cache Invalidation:**
- TTL-based expiration (30 days)
- Manual flush when company policies are updated (e.g., benefits changes during open enrollment)
- Category-scoped invalidation: policy updates in one area (e.g., PTO) trigger cache clear only for that category

## Performance Goals

- **Target Hit Rate:** 65%+
- **Cache Lookup Latency:** < 5ms
- **Cost Reduction:** 70% fewer LLM API calls
- **Precision:** > 95% (cached responses must accurately match user intent)

## Example Queries

**Should Hit Cache (similar meaning):**
- "How many vacation days do I get?" ↔ "What's the PTO allowance?"
- "When is payday?" ↔ "What day do I get paid?"
- "What health insurance plans are available?" ↔ "Tell me about medical coverage options"
- "Can I work from home?" ↔ "What's the remote work policy?"
- "How do I submit an expense report?" ↔ "Where do I file my reimbursement?"
- "What is the maternity leave policy?" ↔ "How long is paid maternity leave?"

**Should Miss Cache (different intent):**
- "How many vacation days do I get?" ✗ "How many sick days do I get?"
- "When is payday?" ✗ "When are annual raises decided?"
- "What's the remote work policy?" ✗ "What's the maternity leave policy?"
- "How do I submit an expense report?" ✗ "What is the meal allowance for travel?"
- "What health insurance plans are available?" ✗ "When is open enrollment?"

## FAQ Categories

| Category | Topics | Approx. Pairs |
|----------|--------|---------------|
| Vacation / PTO | Days off, carryover, requesting time off | 4 |
| Benefits | Health insurance, dental, enrollment, dependents | 4 |
| Salary / Payroll | Payday, pay stubs, direct deposit, raises | 4 |
| Remote Work | WFH policy, full-time remote, home office stipend | 3 |
| Sick Leave / Family Leave | Sick days, maternity, paternity | 3 |
| Expenses / Travel | Expense reports, travel reimbursement, meal allowance | 3 |
| Onboarding | First day, email setup, employee handbook | 3 |
| General | HR contact, company holidays | 2 |
